SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773921770
OL,3,CBurnham: Labour would 'do well to
OL,4,Clisten to' Rayner after criticism of PM
OL,6,F"That would be not just bad policy but
OL,7,Fa breach of trust," she told the event
OL,8,Frun by the centre-left campaign group
OL,9,FMainstream.
OL,11,F"The people already in the system `
OL,12,Fwho made a huge investment ` now fear
OL,13,Ffor their future, they do not have
OL,14,Fstability and do not know what will
OL,15,Fhappen.
OL,17,F"We cannot talk about earning a
OL,18,Fsettlement if we keep moving the
OL,19,Fgoalposts, because moving the
OL,20,Fgoalposts undermines our sense of fair
OL,21,Fplay. It's un-British."
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@AOU}D@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
