OL,3,CBurnham: Labour would 'do well to
OL,4,Clisten to' Rayner after criticism of PM
OL,6,FRayner also warned Labour is now being
OL,7,Fseen by many voters as representing
OL,8,F"the Establishment, not working
OL,9,Fpeople".
OL,11,FThe MP for Ashton-under-Lyne resigned
OL,12,Fas housing secretary and deputy prime
OL,13,Fminister last year after a row over
OL,14,Fher underpayment of stamp duty on a
OL,15,Fnew property.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
